valueString:
Impression:


1. Mild cervical spinal canal stenosis at C6-C7. No high-grade spinal
canal stenosis.


2. Multilevel mild disc disease, uncinate hypertrophy, and facet
arthrosis resulting in multilevel variable but generally mild or
mild-to-moderate neural foraminal stenosis. No high-grade neural
foraminal stenosis.


3. Multiple enhancing masses in the superficial and deep soft tissues of
the neck. There are also multiple T2 signal hyperintensity enhancing
masses along the bilateral cervical neural foramen as described above.
Findings compatible with multiple nerve sheath tumors. No direct
comparison imaging of the neck is available for review to otherwise
assess disease or disease progression.


4. No acute osseous abnormality.
